The next International Category Theory Meeting will take place in Genoa =
(Italy), from Sunday, 21 June, to Saturday, 27 June, 2020, at DIMA, via =
Dodecaneso 35.

Contributions in all aspects of Category Theory are welcome and we =
especially encourage researchers to submit works on its applications as =
well as on its foundations. All talks will be held at DIMA.

At the moment the website

https://sites.google.com/view/ct2020

contains basic information, and will be updated as soon as =
details become available.

Abstract submission is now open and we intend to manage them via =
EasyChair. The deadline for submitting is 20 April, but submissions will =
be handled as continuously as possible; so we encourage prospective =
contributors to submit their abstract as soon as they can. Abstract =
acceptance will be communicated by 12 May at the latest.

Registration will open on 12 March and close on 20 May.

The Scientific Committee consists of

Maria M. Clementino
Marcelo Fiore
Nicola Gambino
Steve Lack
Rory Lucyshyn-Wright
Sandra Mantovani
Mat=C3=ADas Menni (chair)
Christina Vasilakopoulou

To request any specific information write to info.ct2020@gmail.com.

We look forward to seeing you in Genoa in the summer!

The Organizing Committee
Sandra Mantovani
Giuseppe Metere
Eugenio Moggi
Andrea Montoli
Giuseppe Rosolini (chair)=


